sect2.para:
Env is an environment variable which is usable in more templates at a time. $Data{""} is just availabe for one template.
The current user name is: $Env{"Userfirstname"}
Some other common variables are: $Env{"SessionID"} --> the current session id $Env{"Time"} --> the current time e. g. Thu Dec 27 16:00:55 2001 $Env{"CGIHandle"} --> the current CGI handle e. g. index.pl $Env{"UserCharset"} --> the current site charset e. g. iso-8859-1 $Env{"Baselink"} --> the baselink --> index.pl?SessionID=... $Env{"UserFirstname"} --> e. g. Dirk $Env{"UserFirstname"} $Env{"UserLogin"} --> e. g. mgg@x11.org $Env{"UserIsGroup[users]"} = Yes --> user groups (useful for own links) $Env{"UserIsGroup[admin]"} = Yes $Env{"Action"} --> the current action

If you want to include other dtl templates into a template, use the include tag:

# include Copyright.dtl
$Include{"Copyright"}

The html code can be displayed in template blocks in the frontend:

# get article
my %Article = $Self->{TicketObject}->ArticleGet(
    ArticleID => $ArticleID,
);

# file blocks
foreach (qw(From To Cc Subject)) {
    if ($Article{$_}) {
        $Self->{LayoutObject}->Block(
            Name => 'Row',
            Data => {
                Key => $_,
                Value => $Article{$_},
            },
        );
    }
}

# process template
my $HTMLOutput = $Self->{LayoutObject}->Output(
    TemplateFile => 'AgentZoomBody',
    Data => {
        %Article
    },
);
